HEADWORD: Mawworm
<hw>Maw"worm`</hw> <pr>(?)</pr>, <pos>n.</pos> <ety>[<ets>Maw</ets> the
belly + <ets>worm</ets>.]</ety> <fld>(Zool.)</fld> <sd>(a)</sd> <def>Any
intestinal worm found in the stomach, esp. the common round worm
(<spn>Ascaris lumbricoides</spn>), and allied species.</def>
<sd>(b)</sd> <def>One of the larvae of botflies of horses; a
bot.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

